        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 24 at 4:11PM MDT by NWS Pueblo CO</headline>
        <description>At 410 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms near Pinon, or 18 miles north of Pueblo, moving
northeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Fountain, Ellicott, Schriever Space Force Base, Pinon, Hanover,
Pueblo West, and Security-Widefield.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 800 PM MDT for
east central Colorado.</instruction>
